VIENNA BUSINESS REFERENCES.

BHITCH & BRO’S., Practical Carriage and Harness
makers. Manufacturers of all kinds of Carriage
work. We have on hand a good stock of Car-
riages of our own manufacture. We do Nmming,
Repairing, Pamnting, and all kinds of Carriage work.
Shop on Race street.

B. BOSTON, Wheelwright and Undertaker.

‘Wheelwrighting in all its Branches, I Manufac-
ture from the Lightest Bu to Road Wagons,
Repairing done and Solicited, also Undertaking in
all its Branches. Shop on Race street.

THOMAS HIGGINS & SON, Merchants and
Millers. General Dealers in all kinds of Merchan-
dise, Meal and Flour, Lumber of all kinds, Floor-
ing, Peach and Grape Boxes.

DR. 5 8. EWERBL, Physician and Surgeon, will
Practice in Dorchester and Wicomico counties, Md.
All calls promptly attended to Day and Night.
Office on Race street,

DR. EUGENE HODSON, Physician and Surgeon.

J. H. VANB, Dealer in Dry Goods, Groceries, Hats,
Cngs, Boots, Shoes, Hardware, Queensware, Willow
and Woodenware, Toilet Soaps, Fancy Articles,
Drugs, Medicines, Notions, &c. Country Produce
of all kinds taken in exchange for goods, Store.at
Linkwood Station,

CHURCH CREEK BUSINESS
REFERENCES.

GRAHAM & JEFFERSON, Dealers in Dry
Goods, Groceries, Hats, Caps, Boots, Shoes, Hard-
ware, hotions, &c, Country Produce taken in ex-
change for goods at all times. Store at Church
Creek. :

JOHN M, COLSTON, Dealer in Drugs, Medi-
cines, Patent Medicines, Chemicals, Varnishes,
Glass, Putty, Dye Stuffs, Fancy Articles, Perfumery,
Toilet Soaps, Paints, Oils, Notions, &c., and all ar-
ticles usually kept in aCoun:g Drug Store. Pre-
scriptions carefully compounded.

LINTHICUM & S8ON.,, Dealers in Dry Goods,
Groceries, Hats, Caps, Boots, Shoes, Hardware,
Queensware, &c., and ali kinds of goods usually
kept in a first class country store.

OLIVER 8. RICHARDSON, Ship Carpenter,
Contractor and Builder, Allkinds of Ship Carpen-
try done with neatness and dispatch. Contracts
taken at all times.

JESSE C. RICHARDSON, Ship Carpenter, Con-
tractor and Builder. All kinds of Ship Carpentry,
done with neatness and dispatch, Contracts taken
at all times,

T. A. WILLIS, Dealer {in Goods, Groceries,
Hats, Caps, Boots, Shoes, and Notions of all kinds.
Country Produce taken in exchange for goods. Stere
at Williams’ Road near Church Creek.

POWELL & NETTLETON, Proprietors of S.S.
Mill on “ Big Blackwater.” All kinds of lumber
cut to order, Custom work promptly and efficiently
done.

THOMAS KING CARROLL, Physician and
Surgeon. All calls promptly attended to. Office
in Church Creek.

‘W. A. VANE, Ship Carpenter.

V. H.. JONES, Dealer in Dry Goods, Groceries,
Hats, Caps, Boots, Shoes, Hardware, Queensware,
Wooden and Willow-ware, Toilet Soaps, Fancy
Articles, Drugs, Medicines, Notions, &c. Country
Produce taken in exchange for Goods. Store at
Linkwood Station. &

SHERMANN & BENNETT, Owners of Schoon-
er Anna'Ellen,” plying between Vienna and Bal.

timore. A General Freighting Business done.

GEORGE A. HARRIS, Blacksmith. Blacksmithing
done in all its Branches. Wagons neatly Ironed.
Horse-Shoeing a Specialty. Persons having any ||
thing in my line will do well to give me a call. Shop
in Church Creek District, Vienna, Md.

J. 8. VINCENT, Telegraph Operator ; Rail Road
and Express Agent, and Post Master. All business
in my line will receive prompt attention. Persons
\Svill find me at all times at my Office. ,Linkwood

tation.

W. H. PHILLIPS, Blacksmith. Blacksmithing done
in all its Branches, also have all kinds of Wheel-
wrighting done to order, All ms wanting any-
thing in my line will do wali to give me a call.
Work done reasonable. Shop at Linkwood Station.
